Distinct Effects of Thalidomide and Pomalidomide on bFGF, VEGF and IL-6 Expression in RPMI8226 and U266 Cells

To compare the therapeutic effect of thalidomide and pomalidomide, we used RPMI8226 and U266 cells, which are high-grade bFGF expressing human myeloma cell lines [].

Our results showed that the bFGF mRNA levels in RPMI8226 (Figure ) cells and were markedly reduced after being treated with thalidomide for 4 h, even at 0.1 μg/ml and 1 μg/ml concentrations, which were lower than the reported serum concentrations (3–6 μg/ml) at most of the therapeutic doses in clinical patients [].
