('gene expression levels', 'were calculated with', 'method')

Immunofluorescence

Cells grown on glass coverslips were fixed in PBS containing 4% paraformaldehyde for 15 min and then permeabilized with 0.01% Triton X-100 for 30 min at room temperature.
('Cells grown on glass coverslips', 'were fixed in', 'PBS')

The cells were subsequently treated with 0.5 μg of a polyclonal rabbit anti-human bFGF peptide, amino acids 40 to 63, antibody (Abcam) for 30 min at room temperature.
('cells', 'were treated with', 'mg of rabbit bFGF peptide')

Cells were then washed and stained with Alexa Fluor® 488 goat anti-rabbit secondary antibodies (Life Technologies) for another 30 min.
